PHISHING EMAIL SAMPLE ANALYSIS – SAMPLE 5

Subject:
Flipkart Order Payment Confirmation

Sender Email:
billing@flipkart.com

Greeting:
Dear Customer,


EMAIL MESSAGE

Thank you for your recent purchase on Flipkart.

Your payment of ₹24,999 has been successfully
processed for the order placed today.

If you did not authorize this transaction,
please review your order details immediately
by clicking the link below:

http://flipkart-order-verification.com

Failure to review this order within 24 hours
may result in the payment being permanently
processed.

Thank you for shopping with Flipkart.

Flipkart Billing Department


PHISHING INDICATORS IDENTIFIED

1. Suspicious External Link
The URL "http://flipkart-order-verification.com"
is not an official Flipkart domain.

2. Urgent Financial Warning
The email creates panic by mentioning a large
transaction and asking the user to verify it.

3. Generic Greeting
The email uses "Dear Customer" instead of the
user's real name.

4. Verification Through Email Link
Legitimate companies typically ask users to
log into their official website rather than
clicking verification links from emails.


EMAIL CLASSIFICATION
Type: Phishing Email
Risk Level: HIGH


ANALYSIS SUMMARY

This email attempts to impersonate Flipkart and
trick users into clicking a malicious verification
link related to a fake purchase.

If the user enters account credentials on the fake
page, attackers may gain access to the user's
Flipkart account and personal information.

Users should verify purchases by visiting the
official Flipkart website or app directly.
